cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language dialog systems and their ability to learn new facts from user utterances. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves machine learning techniques for interactive learning. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves training a model to learn from user interactions. It may also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves retrieving information from user utterances. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it involves designing a system that interacts with users in a natural way.
